  "detailed_description": "Gravity Waves is a twin stick shoot 'em up in space with realistic gravity against enemies attacking in waves which build from a gentle pace to very very hectic. <br><br> <span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2434510/extras/54f0d328edf57cc3bc0692816710d579.poster.avif?t=1689501305\" width=640 height=340 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2434510/extras/54f0d328edf57cc3bc0692816710d579.webm?t=1689501305\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2434510/extras/54f0d328edf57cc3bc0692816710d579.mp4?t=1689501305\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br><br>Gain extra points for close-up kills and using planets, moons and the sun to slingshot you with their gravity. Wnemies drop health boosts and occaisionally extra lives.<br><br>The gravity takes a little getting used to but it provides gameplay that changes moment by moment and totally keeps you on your toes.<br><br> <span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2434510/extras/55ca7c1cfd8dab548b98909f31f8ef9e.poster.avif?t=1689501305\" width=640 height=340 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2434510/extras/55ca7c1cfd8dab548b98909f31f8ef9e.webm?t=1689501305\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2434510/extras/55ca7c1cfd8dab548b98909f31f8ef9e.mp4?t=1689501305\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br><br>Key features:<br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>wave based shooter<br></li><li>realistic gravity and orbits<br></li><li>old school arcade action<br></li><li>builds from simple encounters to fast paced, quickly changing action<br></li><li>music by @remixedcat</li></ul><br>A demo version is available at ",
